==Kevin Smith== {{Infobox soap character 2|series=Hollyoaks |name= Kevin Smith |portrayer= [[Cameron Crighton]] |creator=[[Paul Marquess]] |years=2010 |first= 29 July 2010 |last= 4 November 2010 |classification=[[List of Hollyoaks characters|Former; regular]] |occupation= [[Student]] }} '''Kevin Smith''', played by [[Cameron Crighton]], first appeared on 29 July 2010. He arrives during a storyline with [[Elliot Bevan]], where Kevin tries to convince everyone he is an alien.<ref>{{Cite book|title=[[Inside Soap]]|date=10â16 July 2010|publisher=([[Hachette Filipacchi MÃ©dias|Hachette Filipacchi UK]])|pages=32}}</ref> He is set to become a fresher student along with [[Lee Hunter]], [[Doug Carter]], [[Jamil Fadel]] and [[Leanne Holiday]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Watch Video - Interview: Cameron Crighton|url=http://www.e4.com/video/goUQqfADq2dKCwWiVxSDQ/play.e4|work=[[E4 (channel)|E4]]|publisher=[[Channel 4|Channel 4 Television Corporation]]|accessdate=2010-07-15|date=July 2010}}</ref>
Information on the character first surfaced during Paul Marquess' reinvention of the serial. The storyline was publicised by the media, who described it as an odd alien storyline.<ref name="alien">{{Cite web|last=Love|first=Ryan|title=Hollyoaks character 'to befriend alien'|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/soaps/s13/hollyoaks/news/a223753/hollyoaks-character-to-befriend-alien.html|work=[[Digital Spy]]|publisher=([[Hachette Filipacchi MÃ©dias|Hachette Filipacchi UK]])|accessdate=21 July 2010|date=6 June 2009<!--|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5uGkhoiqp|archivedate=15 November 2010-->}}</ref> At that point in time there was no official confirmation of the storyline being true, until actress [[Hollie-Jay Bowes]] who played [[Michaela McQueen]] confirmed details of the plot, which contributed in her dismisal from the serial.<ref name="sack">{{Cite web|last=Green|first=Kris|title=Hollie-Jay Bowes sacked from 'Hollyoaks'|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/soaps/s13/hollyoaks/news/a232110/hollie-jay-bowes-sacked-from-hollyoaks.html|work=[[Digital Spy]]|publisher=([[Hachette Filipacchi MÃ©dias|Hachette Filipacchi UK]])|accessdate=2010-09-12|date=25 June 2010<!--|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5uGka0p24|archivedate=15 November 2010-->}}</ref> Actor Cameron Crighton was cast in the role and he expressed his delight to be joining a show that was widely known and stated he it took ages to sink in.<ref name="vid">{{Cite web|title=Watch video - Interview: Cameron Crighton|url=http://www.e4.com/video/goUQqfADq2dKCwWiVxSDQ/play.e4|work=[[E4 (channel)|E4]]|publisher=([[Channel 4|Channel 4 Television Corporation]])|accessdate=21 July 2010|date=July 2010<!--|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5uGkRRe7M|archivedate=15 November 2010-->}}</ref> It was later revealed that Crighton had finished filming with the serial by September 2010.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Littlejohn|first=Georgina|title=Hollyoaks' Carley Stenson says goodbye to the soap with fancy dress cast party in Liverpool|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-1311304/Hollyoaks-Carley-Stenson-says-goodbye-soap-fancy-dress-cast-party-Liverpool.html?ito=feeds-newsxml|work=[[Daily Mail]]|publisher=([[Associated Newspapers{{!}}Associated Newspapers Ltd]])|accessdate=2010-09-13|date=12 September 2010<!--|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5uGkUvPX3|archivedate=15 November 2010-->}}</ref> Crighton's final scenes were due to be aired on the 9 November 2010.<ref name="soapshow">{{cite web|title=Hollyoaks Catch Up|url=http://www.thesoapshow.com/soaps/hollyoaks-catch-up.htm|work=Thesoapshow.com|publisher=The Soap Show|accessdate=2010-11-14<!--|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5uGkCwoFa|archivedate=15 November 2010-->|date=1 November 2010}}</ref> But they did not make the final cut.
On his arrival, after he befriends [[Elliot Bevan]] he begins telling him that he is desperate to get home to his planet which he claims to have been sent from. [[Nancy Hayton]] and [[Kris Fisher]] have a hard time believing this. He later makes friends with a young [[Tom Cunningham]] and cheers him up and helping him believe in life after death. In Fresher's week, Kevin and Doug clash, meanwhile the other students think he is odd. He sees Leanne and Doug kiss and decides to tell Lee of their infidelity. Doug then finds out some secrets about Kevin's past. Despite his housemates finding out the truth, Kevin still keeps up the pretence of being an alien and attempts to build a [[Beacon]], with the help of Elliot, in order for his parents to find him. Elliot finds Kevin's birth certificate and works out the truth. When the beacon is finally turned on he gives Tom a telescope as a gift. Kevin also secures Elliot a new job at [[NASA]] before leaving Hollyoaks. {{-}}
