==Brendan Brady== {{Main|Brendan Brady}} '''Brendan Brady''', played by Irish actor [[Emmett J. Scanlan]], made his first on-screen appearance on 5 August 2010.<ref>{{citenews|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/soaps/s13/hollyoaks/spoilers/a250151/2879-zak-threatens-to-contact-the-police.html|title=2879: Zak threatens to contact the police|work=[[Digital Spy]]|publisher=[[Hachette Filipacchi MÃ©dias|Hachette Filipacchi UK]]|first=Daniel|last=Kilkelly|date=5 August 2010|accessdate=2010-12-01}}</ref> Scanlan's casting was announced on 25 June 2010.<ref name="confirms"/> He is the brother of [[Cheryl Brady]] ([[Bronagh Waugh]]).<ref name="confirms"/><ref name="new bad boy">{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/soaps/s13/hollyoaks/news/a215499/new-bad-boy-for-hollyoaks.html |title=New bad boy for Hollyoaks |work=[[Digital Spy]]|publisher=([[Hachette Filipacchi MÃ©dias|Hachette Filipacchi UK]]) |author=Daniel Kilkelly and Kris Green |date=20 April 2010 |accessdate=2010-12-01<!-- |archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5td4LPnLr|archivedate=20 October 2010 -->}}</ref> Brendan has been described as a "dodgy dealer" and "a complex character".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://holysoap.five.tv/hollyoaks/news/brendans-just-misunderstood-9806 |title=Brendan's just misunderstood! |work=[[Holy Soap]] |publisher=([[Channel 5 (UK)|Channel 5 Broadcasting]]) |date=17 September |accessdate=2010-12-01<!-- |archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5td2XhKwI|archivedate=20 October 2010 -->}}</ref>
==Veronica== {{Infobox soap character 2|series=Hollyoaks |name= Veronica |portrayer= Lynsey McLaren |introducer= [[Paul Marquess]] |classification=[[List of Hollyoaks characters|Former; recurring]] |years=2010 |first= 6 August 2010 |last = 8 October 2010 }} '''Veronica''', played by Lynsey McLaren, first appeared on 9 August 2010. She is first seen outside The Dog in the Pond when [[Brendan Brady]] catches her eye. Brendan offers to buy her a drink and she accepts. She then gets talking to [[Malachy Fisher]] and they share a couple of drinks together. She later goes home with Malachy, kissing him and they head upstairs. She ties him to his bed, tricking him into thinking they were about to have sex, when she actually did it to trap him whilst she could steal money and items of jewellery from the McQueens. She admits Malachy is a nice person, kissing him before leaving him tied up.<ref name="wavee"/> Veronica steals everything from the McQueen home then went on to rob Evissa. Malachy manages to track her down, and ties her up. She plays on his marital problems with [[Mercedes McQueen]] to get him to leave the keys to the van full of stolen goods, but later, he sends Mercedes to the address, and she attacks Veronica for helping break up her marriage. Brendan, who had been working with Veronica, shows up later, and Veronica berates him for getting her involved with insane Mercedes.
Veronica later blackmails Brendan, who sets her up to get arrested by [[Carmel Valentine]]. She makes another appearance when Brendan uses her to try and split up [[Rae Wilson]] and [[Ste Hay]]. {{-}}
==Trish Minniver== {{Infobox soap character 2|series=Hollyoaks |name= Trish Minniver |portrayer= Paula Wolfenden |creator=[[Paul Marquess]] |years=2010â |first= 10 August 2010 |classification=[[List of Hollyoaks characters|Present; recurring]] |daughters=[[Mitzeee Minniver]] |nieces= [[Heidi Costello]]<br>Wendy Blissett |halfsisters=Joan Blisset |relatives=[[Riley Costello]]<br>[[Seth Costello]]<br>[[Jason Costello]]<br> Bobby |born=10 August 1971 }} '''Trish Minniver''', played by Paula Wolfenden, is the mother of [[Mitzeee Minniver]], who arrives on her birthday to see her family. It is revealed that she has bitter feelings towards her niece "that she treated like a sister" [[Heidi Costello]], this is because Trish used to date [[Carl Costello]] before he left her for Heidi. She appears to be using her daughter Mitzeee in her plan to make Carl and his familys life hell. Trish reappears at Christmas 2010 with Mitzeee and makes peace with Heidi and Carl, before befriending [[Myra McQueen]]. Trish encourages Heidi to be more accepting of her transgender son [[Jason Costello]].<ref name="wavee">{{Cite web|title=Hollyoaks - Waveguide TV and Radio News|url=http://www.waveguide.co.uk/hollyoaks.htm|work=Waveguide|accessdate=28 July 2010|date=26 July 2010}}</ref>
In May 2011 Mitzeee is shocked to discover tat Ethan has arrested Trish, and blackmails her into getting Warren to confess to the murder of [[Louise Summers]] or Trish will be sent down for 2 year's. However this later backfires and Trish is released without charge. {{-}}
==Alistair Longford== {{Infobox soap character 2|series=Hollyoaks |name= Alistair Longford |portrayer= Terence Harvey |introducer=[[Paul Marquess]] |years=2010 |first= 24 August 2010 |last= 24 September 2010 |classification=[[List of past Hollyoaks characters|Former; recurring]] |born= 1938 |death= 2011 |occupation= Retired |sons=Teddy Longford |mother=[[Blanche Longford]] |granddaughters=[[India Longford]]<br/>[[Texas Longford]] |wife=Pamela Longford<br> [[Cindy Hutchinson]] (2010&ndash;11) }} '''Alistair Longford''', played by Terence Harvey, was a wealthy pensioner and grandfather of [[Texas Longford|Texas]] and [[India Longford]] who first appears when he chokes on food at Il Gnosh. He is saved by [[Myra McQueen]] using the [[Heimlich maneuver]]. Myra tells Alistair that [[Cindy Hutchinson]] was responsible for saving him, not realising his reward. Believing Cindy was responsible, Alistair gives Cindy a handful of Â£50 notes. This leaves Myra feeling insolent and upset. Alistair and Cindy grow closer until they begin a relationship.
Alistair charms Cindy. However, after she realises that he is India's grandfather, she leaves. After this event, he visits his granddaughters to discuss their allowance and Texas's spending issues. The next day, India tells Cindy that her grandfather lives in [[Sandbanks]], a highly upmarket area. Cindy then realises that Alistair is a millionaire and returns to him to try and rekindle their relationship. Just then, Alistair asks Cindy to marry him. Cindy is left gobsmacked and speechless. After numerous attempts to sabotage the wedding from his mother [[Blanche Longford|Blanche]], Alistair and Cindy marry and leave for their honeymoon.
Cindy returns to Hollyoaks on 9 March 2011 and explains that during their honeymoon in [[Switzerland]], Alistair fell of an [[Mountain|Alp]] and died. {{-}}
