==Rob O'Connor== {{Infobox soap character 2|series=Hollyoaks |name = Rob O'Connor |portrayer = Gary Cargill |introducer = [[Paul Marquess]] |years = 2010â2011 |classification=[[List of Hollyoaks characters|Former; regular]] |first = 1 September 2010 |last = 10 January 2011 |wife = [[Diane O'Connor]] |romances=Morag |sons = [[Finn O'Connor (Hollyoaks)|Finn O'Connor]] |daughters = [[Sinead O'Connor (Hollyoaks)|Sinead O'Connor]] |granddaughters = Bella Sharpe |occupation= [[Headmaster]] }} '''Robert "Rob" O'Connor''', played by Gary Cargill, is a character who arrived on 1 September 2010 along with the rest of his family. Rob and his family move to Hollyoaks due to his new job as deputy headmaster. However, soon after, daughter [[Sinead O'Connor (Hollyoaks)|Sinead O'Connor]] knocks the headteacher unconscious with the water bucket trick. Rob is promoted to acting head. Rob's wife [[Diane O'Connor|Diane]] steals a baby from a hospital. With the help of [[Lynsey Nolan]] and Sinead, Rob convinces Diane to give the baby back.
[[Amber Sharpe]] becomes pregnant by Finn, but starts to write in her diary saying that Rob is the father. Amber kisses Rob, which is seen by [[Eva Strong]]. Eva then steals Ambers diary and threatens to blackmail him with it. Feeling sorry for Rob, Eva's daughter [[Anita Roy]] decides to give him the diary so he can dispose of it, but Anita is unaware that Eva had taken out the important pages. Anita takes Rob back to her flat to try find the missing pages, Eva returns home and finds Rob alone in the flat with Anita, Eva then calls the police and has Rob arrested. Sinead is devastated that he is arrested, and Diane informs Sinead that Rob started seeing her when she was his 15-year-old student. Diane also tells her that Sinead and Finn's real mother is still alive. Sinead is furious with Rob for not telling her. Diane and Rob decide to split up and Rob plans to take Sinead and Finn away with him, but Sinead decides to stay with Diane, so Rob leaves. {{-}}
==Trent Harvard== {{Infobox soap character 2|series=Hollyoaks |name=Trent Harvard |portrayer=Olivier Blanc |introducer=[[Paul Marquess]] |years=2010 |first= 26 August 2010 |last = 10 September 2010 |classification=[[List of past Hollyoaks characters|Former; recurring]] }}
Trent Harvard is a character who arrived during Hollyoaks: Freshers, played by Olivier Blanc. It is soon revealed that he used to date India Longford. He is described as "nasty and manipulative" and is set to cause trouble for Texas Longford.[62]
Trent notices Texas at a music festival after she is thrown out. He gets her free entry and they begin to discuss his failed relationship with India. They begin to flirt and it becomes apparent they have an attraction. India is annoyed at Texas for spending time with her ex. He asks Texas to visit him in his hotel room, they spend the night together. Trent starts blackmailing Texas, that if she doesn't give him money, he will show a video of him and Texas having sex to India.
Texas fools him by handing him a envelope filled with paper instead of money. After this he Emails India the video footage. She and Texas argue, but she forgives her knowing Trent is trying to come between them. {{-}}
==Viv== {{Infobox soap character 2|series=Hollyoaks |name=Viv |portrayer=Venetia Fawcett |introducer=[[Paul Marquess]] |Duration 2010 |first= 2 September 2010 |classification=[[List of past Hollyoaks characters|Former; recurring]] }}
Vivienne is a character whom arrives during Hollyoaks: Freshers, played by Venetia Fawcett. Viv is described as wanting to show everyone a good time, but not who she makes out to be.[63]
When Viv hitchhikes, the male students take an instant liking to her. Charlotte however is wary of her, later Jamil takes a dislike to her. Charlotte and Viv kiss, although Charlotte feels intimidated. Charlotte later decides to ignore her and have a good time. Viv can speak French and English. Viv then tries to steal from Charlotte, but Dave ruins her plan. She steals Doug's camper van. She later returns and tries to get Charlotte to leave with her, but Charlotte punches her and they fight. Viv then leaves. {{-}}
==Jamil Fadel== {{Infobox soap character 2|series=Hollyoaks |name=Jamil Fadel |portrayer=Sikander Malik |introducer=[[Paul Marquess]] |years=2010â11 |classification=[[List of Hollyoaks characters#Past characters|Former; regular]] |first= 13 September 2010 |last= 9 September 2011 |occupation= [[Student]]/radio presenter |brothers=Rashad Fadel }} '''Jamil Fadel''', played by Sikander Malik, arrived in September 2010 as part of the new students. Jamil is characterised as being "very nice". Jamil arrives in Hollyoaks along with [[Doug Carter]] after their trip to France. He moves into Student Halls alongside Doug, [[Jem Costello]], [[Lee Hunter]], [[Leanne Holiday]], [[Kevin Smith]] and [[Darren Osborne]]. Jamil soon asks [[Charlotte Lau]] out on a date, but is embarrassed when he realises that she is a lesbian. After failed attempts with Charlotte, [[India Longford]] sleeps with Jamil following their growing friendship. Meanwhile, [[Brendan Brady]] steals goods from the halls in return for drugs which he gives to Doug Carter. Later, Jamil is confronted by a woman. She is revealed to be Jamil's wife, [[Lanika Fadel]]. Jamil reveals that he and Lanika are however not legally married, as he fled on the wedding day. After talking, Lanika and Jamil agree to get married. However, he lies to his friends by saying it was an arranged marriage. Jamil and Lanika agree not to go through with the wedding. Jamil has a one night stand with [[Mercedes Fisher]] and is shocked when he discovers she may be HIV positive. He has a brief relationship with [[Texas Longford]] although she soon after ends it. Jamil and Lee are offered jobs as radio presenters from the college dean and they later hire nurse [[Lynsey Nolan]] as the agony aunt for their show thus putting her in great danger as murderer [[Silas Blissett]] is not impressed with her advice.
In September, he has a go at his housemates for their selfish behaviour and soon, because of what he said, decides to leave his course and work for his brother. His housemates catch up with him, make amends and see him off.
Malik revealed via Twitter on June 23 that he was departing Hollyoaks after a year on screen, and will depart the series on 9 September 2011.<ref name="Jamil departure">{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/soaps/s13/hollyoaks/news/a326453/hollyoaks-actor-confirms-jamil-departure.html|title='Hollyoaks' actor confirms Jamil departure|work=[[Digital Spy]]|publisher=[[Hachette Filipacchi UK]]|date=23 June 2011|first=Daniel|last=Kilkelly|accessdate=23 June 2011}}</ref>
