==Macca== {{Infobox soap character 2|series=Hollyoaks |name=Macca |portrayer=Drew Dillon |introducer=[[Paul Marquess]] |years=2010 |first= 12 October 2010 |last= 22 November 2010 |classification=[[List of Hollyoaks characters|Former; recurring]] |aunts=[[Eileen Brady]] |cousins=[[Declan Brady]]<br> Paddy Brady <br> Niamh Brady }} '''Macca''', played by Drew Dillon, arrived on 12 October 2010.<ref>{{cite web|last=Dillon|first=Drew|title=Drew Dillon Official|url=http://drewdillon.co.uk/|work=drewdillon.co.uk|accessdate=2010-09-19|date=7 August 2010}}</ref> The nephew of [[Brendan Brady]]'s wife [[Eileen Brady|Eileen]]. It becomes clear that Macca had been having an affair with Brendan. Macca becomes friends with [[Ste Hay]] Brendan's new secret boyfriend. Brendan has Macca beaten up and tells everyone he went back home to Ireland. Macca returns a few weeks later at the hospital where he has been staying since the beating. Brendan threatens Macca to go home however Macca makes it clear he is not going anywhere as he is still in love with Brendan. Macca takes Ste to a gay bar where they kiss. {{-}}
==Danny Houston== {{Infobox soap character 2|series=Hollyoaks ||name=Danny Houston |portrayer=[[Darren Day]] |introducer=[[Paul Marquess]] |years=2010 |first= 19 October 2010 |last= 28 December 2010 |classification=[[List of past Hollyoaks characters|Former; recurring]] |occupation= Nightclub owner (2010) |death=28 December 2010 }} '''Danny Houston''', played by [[Darren Day]], is a friend of [[Brendan Brady]] ([[Emmett J. Scanlan]]) and partner in ownership of club Chez Chez with Brendan's sister [[Cheryl Brady]] ([[Bronagh Waugh]]). He first appeared on 19 October 2010.<ref name="wr">{{Cite web|last=Love|first=Ryan|title=Darren Day joins 'Hollyoaks'|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/soaps/s13/hollyoaks/news/a277965/darren-day-joins-hollyoaks.html|work=[[Digital Spy]]|publisher=([[Hachette Filipacchi MÃ©dias|Hachette Filipacchi UK]])|accessdate=21 September 2010|date=21 September 2010}}</ref>
The character was first announced in September 2010, with [[West End theatre|London West End]] star Darren Day being cast in the role.<ref name="darren interview">{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/soaps/s13/hollyoaks/interviews/a282461/darren-day-danny-houston-hollyoaks.html |title=Darren Day (Danny Houston, 'Hollyoaks') |first=Daniel |last=Kilkelly |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=([[Hachette Filipacchi MÃ©dias|Hachette Filipacchi UK]]) |date=16 October 2010 |accessdate=2010-12-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/soaps/s13/hollyoaks/scoop/a282462/more-hollyoaks-chat-from-darren-day.html |title=More 'Hollyoaks' chat from Darren Day |first=Daniel |last=Kilkelly |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=([[Hachette Filipacchi MÃ©dias|Hachette Filipacchi UK]]) |date=16 October 2010 |accessdate=2010-12-01}}</ref> It was revealed that Danny would appear in only one episode, returning later in the year.<ref name="darren interview"/> Of his casting and character, Day stated, "I've really enjoyed filming with ''Hollyoaks'' and I'm excited about coming back. Danny is the type of character any actor would kill to play and the part has been made even better as I'm working with great talent such as Claire, Emmett and Bronagh."<ref name="wr"/> He later spoke about the character in an interview with [[Digital Spy]], "There is going to be no-one badder than Danny Houston â he's about as bad as it gets and is the epitome of a soap villain really. I've been told that some soap magazines are nicknaming him Dirty Dan! For me, that's really exciting."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/soaps/s13/hollyoaks/news/a282400/darren-day-teases-hollyoaks-role.html |title=Darren Day teases 'Hollyoaks' role |first=Daniel |last=Kilkelly |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=([[Hachette Filipacchi MÃ©dias|Hachette Filipacchi UK]]) |date=18 October 2010 |accessdate=2010-12-01}}</ref>
Series producer Paul Marquess also described the character: "Danny Houston is a dangerous but very charming character who makes an aggressive impact in his first episodes. Darren plays the part brilliantly and Iâm delighted that we're able to bring him back later this year."<ref name="wr"/> Scanlan mentioned Day was a "great addition to the cast".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/soaps/s13/hollyoaks/scoop/a282709/more-from-hollyoaks-star-emmett-scanlan.html |title=More from 'Hollyoaks' star Emmett Scanlan |first=Daniel |last=Kilkelly |work=[[Digital Spy]] |publisher=([[Hachette Filipacchi MÃ©dias|Hachette Filipacchi UK]]) |date=18 October 2010 |accessdate=2010-12-01}}</ref>
===Storylines===
Before he arrives on-screen, Danny is made a silent partner of Chez Chez with [[Cheryl Brady]]. [[Carl Costello]] ([[Paul Opacic]]) tells [[Malachy Fisher]] ([[Glen Wallace]]) that he knows of Danny and warns him that he is potentially dangerous. Danny later accompanies Brendan and [[Jacqui McQueen]] ([[Claire Cooper]]) for lunch. After which, he asks to take Jacqui out. He offers to meet Jacqui numerous times and the pair start a relationship, annoying [[Rhys Ashworth]] ([[Andrew Moss]]). In Danny's first on-screen appearance, he arrives in Hollyoaks to visit Chez Chez. Danny becomes jealous of Jacqui and Rhys, and shouts at her, after which she angrily warns him not to talk to her as he did. He later catches Jacqui and Rhys kissing, before threatening them. Jacqui later dumps Danny and embarks on a relationship with Rhys. Danny swears he will make their lives hell.
Danny attends a poker game along with Brendan, Rhys and Jacqui and soon realises that Jacqui is cheating. Danny's thugs take Rhys and hang him upside down from a balcony. Danny tells Jacqui that she has 24 hours to pay him a sum of money or he will kill Rhys. However, Danny gives Jacqui another option, if she sleeps with Danny, he will wipe the debt and give her money she needs. Jacqui agrees to sleep with Danny, but she explains she loves Rhys. Danny decides to let Jacqui go. Danny reveals to Brendan he knows he is gay, and tells him he killed an old lover of Brendan's in the past. Brendan and Danny decide to kill [[Warren Fox]] ([[Jamie Lomas]]) after they find him in Chez Chez. Brendan, however, double crosses Danny and makes a deal with Warren. Warren and Brendan tell Danny to sign his half of Chez Chez to Brendan, to which he agrees. However, Danny threatens to reveal Brendan is gay and to kill his lover [[Ste Hay]] ([[Kieron Richardson]]). An angry Brendan lashes out and beats Danny with a hammer, which causes his death. Warren and Brendan then dump Danny's body in a river. On 18 March 2011, Ste goes fishing with Leah and Lucas at the river. When he thinks he has caught a fish, he reels his line in and discovers he has caught Danny's body at the end of his rod. Ste then calls the police. {{-}}
==Liam McAllister== {{Infobox soap character 2|series=Hollyoaks |name=Liam McAllister |portrayer=Chris Overton |introducer=[[Paul Marquess]] |years=2010 |first=20 October 2010 |last=30 November 2010 |spinoffs=''[[Hollyoaks Later]]'' |classification=[[List of past Hollyoaks characters|Former; recurring]] |brothers=Nathan McAllister |romances=[[Jem Costello]]<br>[[Mitzeee Minniver]] }} '''Liam McAllister''', played by Chris Overton, first appeared 20 October 2010 as [[Jem Costello]]'s ex-boyfriend.<ref name="ft">{{cite web|last=Overton|first=Chris|title=Chris Overton Official|url=http://www.freewebs.com/chrisoverton/|work=chrisoverton.co.uk|accessdate=2010-10-01}}</ref> The character was mentioned several times before his appearance. Liam was a footballer, who went out with Jem. His football career ended after Jem's father [[Carl Costello]] broke Liam's leg for going out with her.
Liam arrives in Hollyoaks, where he spies on Jem's brothers, [[Riley Costello|Riley]] and [[Seth Costello|Seth]]. Jem and Liam go on a date, and Jem explains why she left him. Liam then invites Riley and Seth to a cage fighting party, where Liam is fighting. At the party, Liam and older brother Nathan plot their revenge on the Costellos. At a house party later in the night, Liam drowns Seth in a jacuzzi. However, he survives. Meanwhile, Riley is drugged. Nathan locks Seth and Riley in a cage and forces them to fight, as Carl is tied up by a noose. Seth and Riley reluctantly fight each other. However, Nathan's girlfriend Sami enters and frees them. Seth, Riley and Carl leave and run through woods. Liam and Nathan follow with a gun. They follow onto a rooftop and Nathan falls onto a spike, killing him, as Liam is arrested. Liam returns and rekindles his relationship with Jem, plotting to destroy Carl by getting [[Mitzeee Minniver]] to sleep with him. However, Liam cheats on Jem with Mitzeee. {{-}}
'''Nathan Mcallister''' Nathan apears in Hollyoaks later and kidnaps carl costello. He forces seth and riley to cagefight and they do but are reluctant. Carl escapes and him,riley and seth run through a woods, and nathan and brother liam have a gun. Then on a roof nathan is about to break carl's legs as he broe liams legs, but seth pushes nathan and he falls into an oil tank, and is impaled on a spike, dying.
==Fern== {{Infobox soap character 2|series=Hollyoaks |name=Fern |portrayer=Amy Gavin |introducer=[[Paul Marquess]] |years=2010-11 |first=25 October 2010 |last=6 January 2011 |classification=[[List of past Hollyoaks characters|Former; recurring]] |spinoffs=''[[Hollyoaks Later]]'' }} '''Fern''', played by Amy Gavin, arrived on 25 October 2010<ref name="wavess"/> and appeared in ''[[Hollyoaks Later]]''.
Fern discovers [[Jasmine Costello]] is transgender, and threatens to reveal the secret to her family after Jasmine rejects a kiss from Fern. Fern accidentally stabs [[Bart McQueen]] during a fight and frames Jasmine's alter-ego 'Jason'. Jasmine's brother [[Seth Costello]] asks Fern to go with him as his date to the school disco, to annoy Jasmine. Later, at the school disco, Fern provokes Jasmine further by threatening to reveal her secret, yet again, on the sound system, as she had a copy of the recording on CD. Fern uses this to blackmail Jasmine to expose her secret, but along with Bart, Jasmine reports her to the police, forcing her to tell the truth about Jason. Despite Jasmine's attempt to tell the whole family about it, Seth meets Fern where she tells him all about Jasmine being Jason. Fern appears a few weeks later, when she apologises and tells Bart and Jason that she will plead guilty at her trial but only if they say that Bart's stabbing was an accident. After a heart-to-heart with Fern, Jason tells her she should come out as lesbian. {{-}}
==Logan Fairhurst== {{Infobox soap character 2|series=Hollyoaks |name=Logan Fairhurst |portrayer=Thomas Sean Hughes |creator=[[Paul Marquess]] |years=2010 |first=25 October 2010 |last=1 November 2010 |classification=[[List of past Hollyoaks characters|Former; Recurring]] |occupation=[[Police constable]] }} '''Logan Fairhurst''', played by Thomas Sean Hughes, is a character that arrived on 25 October 2010, during ''Hollyoaks Later''. He takes a shine to [[Theresa McQueen]] straight away. He is a policeman and best friend of [[Riley Costello]].
Logan first sees Theresa whilst at the cage fighting event. He is instantly attracted to Theresa as he sees her from across the room. Riley tells her that he is a footballer. Logan and Theresa grow close during a party at a footballer's house and eventually share a kiss. However, pregnant Theresa's waters break and she goes into labour. Logan arrives at hospital to see Theresa, but Theresa's cousin [[Jacqui McQueen]] makes her end their relationship in worry they may be found out for Theresa's murder of [[Calvin Valentine]]. {{-}}
==Kathleen-Angel McQueen== {{Infobox soap character 2 | series = Hollyoaks | name = Kathleen-Angel McQueen | portrayer = Uncredited | years = 2010â | introducer = [[Paul Marquess]] | first = 29 October 2010 | born = 30 October 2010 | spinoffs = ''[[Hollyoaks Later]]'' | classification=[[List of Hollyoaks characters#Recurring characters|Present; recurring]] | home = [[List of Hollyoaks locations#26 Leigh Road|26 Leigh Road]] | father = [[Calvin Valentine]] | mother = [[Theresa McQueen]] | grandmothers = [[Diane Valentine]]<br> [[Kathleen McQueen]] | grandfathers= [[Leo Valentine]]<br> [[William Alexander (Hollyoaks)|William Alexander]] | aunts= [[Sasha Valentine]]<br> [[Lauren Valentine]] <br> [[Jacqui McQueen]] <br> [[Mercedes McQueen]] <br> [[Emily Alexander (Hollyoaks)|Emily Alexander]] <br> [[Myra McQueen]] (great) | uncles= [[Danny Valentine]]<br> [[Sonny Valentine]] | cousins = Bobby<!--Do not add a second name - Wait until Hollyoaks or another source confirms that his second is Costello or McQueen.--> |relatives [[Niall Rafferty]] <br> [[Tina Reilly]] <br> [[Carmel Valentine]] <br> [[John Paul McQueen]] <br> [[Michaela McQueen]] <br> [[Bart McQueen]] <br> [[Max McQueen]] }} '''Kathleen-Angel McQueen''' is the daughter of [[Calvin Valentine]] ([[Ricky Whittle]]) and [[Theresa McQueen]] ([[Jorgie Porter]]), who is born on-screen in episode five of ''[[Hollyoaks Later]]'', broadcast on 29 October 2010.
After her birth, Theresa's cousin [[Carmel Valentine]] ([[Gemma Merna]]) visits her in hospital and tells Theresa that she wants to raise the baby as her own daughter, as Theresa had killed Calvin months before, but Myra says no. Carmel wants to get the baby baptised as "Angel Valentine", but the girl's grandmother [[Kathleen McQueen]] has other ideas, and, while Carmel is out, she locks [[Myra McQueen|Myra]] and [[Mercedes Fisher|Mercedes]] upstairs while she has her granddaughter christened as "Kathleen Khloe McQueen" to spite Carmel. Though they rename her Kathleen-Angel
On the 8th of February 2011, Theresa decides to leave with Kathleen-Angel and they try to leave the next day when they are kidnapped by [[Kyle Ryder]] ([[Neil Toon]]). They are held hostage in an old bank and when Theresa tries to run away and ends up on the roof, Kyle takes them back inside and ties Theresa to a chair. When Carmel and [[Ethan Scott]] turn up after a distressed phone call from Theresa, Ethan and Kyle fight and Ethan falls down a lift shaft and breaks his leg. Kyle is left holding baby Kathleen-Angel, but he is then shot by [[Warren Fox]] ([[Jamie Lomas]]) and both Kyle and Kathleen-Angel end up in the lift sharf too. Ethan passes Kathleen-Angel to Warren where she is reunited with Theresa and Carmel. Then whilst in hospital, she takes a turn for the worse and is moved to intensive care and placed on life support and Theresa blames herself for everything. Calvin then appears to Carmel as a ghost holding the baby saying she is safe. In the hospital the doctor decides to take out Kathleen-Angel's breathing tube to see if she can do it unaided. The test is successful as she begins to breathe on her own.
==Trev Costello== {{Infobox soap character 2 |series=Hollyoaks |name=Trev Costello |portrayer=[[Scott Neal]] |introducer=[[Paul Marquess]] |years=2010 |first=5 November 2010 |last=31 December 2010 |classification=[[List of past Hollyoaks characters|Former; recurring]] |occupation=[[Interior designer]] |wife=Tanya Costello |childrens= 3 unknown |brothers=[[Carl Costello]] |nephews=[[Riley Costello]]<br>[[Seth Costello]]<br>[[Jason Costello]]<br>Bobby (great nephew) |nieces=[[Jem Costello]] }} '''Trevor "Trev" Costello''' (known as '''Alphonse'''), played by [[Scott Neal]], first appears on 5 November 2010.
Trev introduces himself as a camp French interior designer named Alphonse. He redecorates the kitchen and living area of the Costellos' house in [[The Dog in the Pond]].<ref>http://www.waveguide.co.uk/hollyoaks.htm</ref> His nephew [[Seth Costello]] convinces [[Duncan Button]] that Alphonse fancies him. He later appears when [[Cheryl Brady]] hires him to redecorate Chez Chez at the SU Bar. Cheryl's brother [[Brendan Brady]] is homophobic towards Alphonse and tries to attack him when Alphonse suggests Brendan is gay. Trev sleeps (still posing as Alphonse) with Cheryl. The day after his nephew [[Riley Costello]] convinces him to come clean about who he really is to Cheryl. He reveals to Cheryl his name is Trev and is married with three kids.
When Cheryl invites Trev for a drink on New Year's Eve, he agrees. However, they kiss passionately until Trev realises his mistake and regrets it causing him to leave, leaving Cheryl heartbroken. Trevor hasn't appeared since. {{-}}
==Ethan Scott== {{Infobox soap character 2 |series=Hollyoaks |name=Ethan Scott |portrayer=[[Craig Vye]]|introducer=[[Paul Marquess]] |first=8 December 2010 |born=18 July <ref>http://www.digitalspy.ie/soaps/s13/hollyoaks/spoilers/a326986/3126-the-net-closes-in-on-two-timing-ethan.html</ref> |years=2010â |classification=[[List of Hollyoaks characters|Present; regular]] |home=3 Oakdale Drive |occupation=Detective constable }} '''Detective Constable Ethan Scott''', played by [[Craig Vye]], first appears on 8 December 2010.<ref name="signings">{{cite web|last=Kilkelly|first=Daniel|title='Hollyoaks' confirms three new signings|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/soaps/s13/hollyoaks/news/a290960/hollyoaks-confirms-three-new-signings.html|work=[[Digital Spy]]|publisher=([[Hachette Filipacchi MÃ©dias|Hachette Filipacchi UK]])|date=2 December 2010|accessdate=2010-12-02}}</ref>
Ethan arrests and questions [[Warren Fox]], convinced he faked his own death. He goes to question [[Carmel Valentine]], but instead talks to Carmel's cousin [[Theresa McQueen]]. After he catches [[Kathleen McQueen]] trying to use fake money, Ethan takes her to the McQueen's and asks Theresa if she wants to go with him for a drink. Theresa soon takes a shine to him, but when she meets a woman named [[Liberty Savage]] at her school for enrolment, he appears at the school gates; waiting for Liberty. She then identifies him as her fiancÃ©e, leaving Theresa slightly heartbroken. Ethan continues to be suspicious of Theresa. Theresa and her daughter Kathleen Angel were kidnapped by [[Kyle Ryder]], Ethan & Kyle get in a fight which leads to Ethan falling down an elevator shaft breaking his leg. Theresa then tells Ethan that she killed [[Calvin Valentine]].
Theresa and Ethan grow closer and share many kisses, but try to avoid being seen by Liberty. When Liberty's family arrive, her brother, [[Will Savage]] (James Atherton) is set up on a date with Theresa by Liberty, and the two grow very close, much to Ethan's jealousy. However, Will descovers the two kissing and at a hotel room, assaults Ethan. Will soon tells Liberty about the kiss and Liberty dumps Ethan. He and Theresa continue their relationship, but also continues a new relationship with Liberty, and struggles to juggle the two. Theresa confronts Ethan after a text he meant to send to Liberty was sent to Theresa instead. He worms his way out of the problem though. Theresa still doesn't believe him though, so she seeks the help of Dodger - together they find out not only has Ethan been cheating on Theresa with Liberty, he's also cheated on Theresa with Rae.
Liberty, Rae and Theresa begin to play with Ethan's head; with Theresa telling him that she is pregnant with his baby, Rae telling him she has an [[Sexually transmitted disease|STD]] and Liberty telling him she has told her brothers they are back together and have set a date for their wedding. Later, all three girls confront him and Ethan realises they know the truth. He tries to get out of it by telling them nobody is perfect, but they decide to get their revenge on him by gunging him and many of the residents enjoy watching him get pink gunge thrown all over him. The week after, Ethan tries to talk to Liberty but is warned off by Will. Ethan returns and drives while texting Theresa and Liberty. He knocks [[Rob Edwards (Hollyoaks)|Rob Edwards]] over and drives off. He enlists the help of Thesera who gets Warren to repair his car. Rob regains consciousness and Ethan questions him and attempts to blur his memory of the accident. He later threatens Theresa to keep quiet about what she knows.
