==Liberty Savage== {{Main|Liberty Savage}} '''Liberty Savage''' is a [[fictional character]] from the British [[Channel 4]] [[soap opera]] ''[[Hollyoaks]]'', played by actress and singer-songwriter [[Abi Phillips]]. She made her first on-screen appearance on 10&nbsp;December&nbsp;2010.<ref name="epi3">{{cite news|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/soaps/s13/hollyoaks/spoilers/a290478/2970-mercedes-makes-life-tricky-for-carl.html|title=2970: Mercedes makes life tricky for Carl|work=[[Digital Spy]]|publisher=[[Hachette Filipacchi MÃ©dias|Hachette Filipacchi UK]]|last=Kilkelly|first=Daniel|date=10 December 2010|accessdate=22 July 2011}}</ref> Phillips was approached by ''Hollyoaks'' producers after she submitted one of her songs to be played on the show.<ref name="three"/> Following a strong response to the song, producers invited her to audition for the role of Liberty, in which she was successful.<ref name="three">{{cite news|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/soaps/s13/hollyoaks/news/a290960/hollyoaks-confirms-three-new-signings.html|title='Hollyoaks' confirms three new signings|work=[[Digital Spy]]|publisher=[[Hachette Filipacchi MÃ©dias|Hachette Filipacchi UK]]|author=Kilkelly, Daniel|date=2 December 2010|accessdate=10 April 2011}}</ref> Liberty was introduced to ''Hollyoaks'' along with her fiancÃ©, [[Ethan Scott]] (Craig Vye).<ref name="three"/>
Her main storylines have been in the love triangle between Ethan, her and her best friend [[Theresa McQueen]] ([[Jorgie Porter]]).<ref name="nasty">{{cite news|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/soaps/s13/hollyoaks/news/a293018/hollyoaks-newcomer-wont-be-nasty.html|title='Hollyoaks' newcomer 'won't be nasty'|work=[[Digital Spy]]|publisher=[[Hachette Filipacchi MÃ©dias|Hachette Filipacchi UK]]|last=Kilkelly|first=Daniel|date=13 December 2010|accessdate=11 April 2011}}</ref> Phillips said that Ethan is in love with Liberty, but does not love her enough to marry her.<ref name="whats on tv">{{citenews|url=http://www.whatsontv.co.uk/soaps/hollyoaks/interviews/hollyoaks-ethan-loves-theresas-ditzy-moments/12372|title= Hollyoaks' Ethan 'loves Theresa's ditzy moments'|work=[[What's on TV]]|publisher=[[IPC Media]]|date=6 April 2011|accessdate=15 April 2011}}</ref> On her arrival her on-screen family was introduced, her two brothers, [[Dodger Savage|Dodger]] (Danny Mac) and [[Will Savage|Will]] (James Atherton) and her father [[Dirk Savage|Dirk]] ([[David Kennedy]]).<ref name="chaos">{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/soaps/s13/hollyoaks/news/a310241/savage-clan-to-cause-havoc-in-hollyoaks.html|title=Savage clan to cause havoc in 'Hollyoaks'|first=Daniel|last=Kilkelly|work=[[Digital Spy]]|publisher=([[Hachette Filipacchi MÃ©dias|Hachette Filipacchi UK]])|date=21 March 2011|accessdate=12 April 2011}}</ref> Liberty performed at [[T4 on the Beach]], she performed as two people, as while Liberty got her big break, Phillips also performed her own solo material.<ref name="t4">{{cite news|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/soaps/s13/hollyoaks/news/a325579/hollyoaks-to-film-t4-on-the-beach-scenes.html|title='Hollyoaks' to film T4 On The Beach scenes|work=[[Digital Spy]]|publisher=[[Hachette Filipacchi MÃ©dias|Hachette Filipacchi UK]]|last=Kelly|first=Kristy|date=18 June 2011|accessdate=22 July 2011}}</ref>
==Melody Longford== {{Infobox soap character 2|series=Hollyoaks |name=Melody Longford |portrayer=Sandy Hendrickse |introducer=[[Paul Marquess]] |years=2010â2011 |first=28 December 2010 |last=4 February 2011 |born=13 July |classification=[[List of Hollyoaks characters#Present characters|Former; regular]] |occupation=[[Singer]] |husband=Teddy Longford |daughters=[[Texas Longford]]<br>[[India Longford]] }} '''Melody Longford''', played by Sandy Hendrickse,<ref name="tv guide">{{cite web|title=Hollyoaks TV Cast List|url=http://www.tvguide.co.uk/cast.asp?title=Hollyoaks|work=TV Guide UK|accessdate=21 December 2010}}</ref> is [[India Longford|India]] ([[Beth Kingston]]) and [[Texas Longford]]'s (Bianca Hendrickse-Spendlove) mother. She made her first on-screen appearance on 28 December 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/soaps/s13/hollyoaks/spoilers/a294051/2982-texas-is-grief-stricken-over-india.html|title=Texas is grief-stricken over India}}</ref>
When India is murdered and her body is uncovered, Texas tells [[Nancy Hayton]] ([[Jessica Fox]]) her that Melody is arriving. Melody arrives in Hollyoaks village and asks [[Lee Hunter]] ([[Alex Carter (British actor)|Alex Carter]]) for directions. Lee recognises her and realises she was a famous singer in the 1980s. Lee takes Melody to Texas's flat and she signs an autograph for him.
Melody attends India's funeral and leaves after helping Texas grieve over her sisters death. {{-}}
